<h1> Terms of Service </h1>

<p> The PB Stanford Platform (the “<b>Platform </b>”) is a website aimed at supporting organizations to collect participatory budgeting opinions. The Platform is offered by the Stanford Crowdsourced Democracy Team (“<b>SCDT</b>”) at Stanford University (“<b>Stanford</b>”) as part of SCDT’s ongoing research project whose goal is to learn how to best use online technology for crowdsourced decision making and deliberation (the “<b>Research</b>”). The Platform is used by a city, state, foundation or other facilitator (as applicable, the “<b>Organizer</b>”) to organize and run its decision-making process (each, a “<b>Process</b>”) by soliciting input via the Platform from individual participants (e.g. residents, citizens, and other participants) in that Process (collectively, “<b>Participants</b>”). The Organizers and the Participants using this instance of the Platform are collectively referred to as the “<b>User</b>” for purposes of these TOS. The nature and scope of a given Process is determined by its Organizer, and a Process may include authentication, voter registration, one or multiple ballots, research questions, a satisfaction/demographic survey  and other forms of opinion or information gathering by the Organizer or SCDT as described in this TOS.
</p>
<p> By using the Platform, the User accepts and agrees to these TOS. These TOS may be amended by SCDT generally at any time. If you do not agree with any of the updated Terms, don't access or use the Platform.
</p>

<h2> Research Project </h2>
<p> The information SCDT collects from each instance or usage of the Platform, both directly observing and recording the interactions of Participants and any surveys completed before and after the Process, helps SCDT better understand the behavior of Participants in a deliberation or decision-making process and the best way of designing both online tools to facilitate these processes and the processes themselves.
</p>
<p> Any part of the Platform exclusively used for research, as opposed to enabling the Organizer to conduct a Process, will be covered by Stanford’s Institutional Review Board and require consent from the relevant Participants.
</p>
<p> Unless SCDT explicitly agrees otherwise with the applicable Organizer, SCDT reserves the right to discontinue the Research and/or to unilaterally terminate use of the Platform at any time.
</p>

