<h2> Data use </h2>
<p>
Stanford and SCDT take personal privacy seriously. The Platform is designed with the goal of collecting only the personally identifiable information of Users that SCDT determines is reasonably required for the operation and functionality of the Platform, for the purposes of the Process established by its Organizer, and for achieving the learning and other objectives of the Research. Generally speaking, these are groups of data that the Platform collects:
</p>
<ul>
<li>Content-data: data streams of all actions of the Participant while on the Platform or participating in the Process (i.e., everything that a Participant does, says, posts, reads or clicks on). These data streams are captured and transmitted to SCDT or its service provider as part of and by the normal operation and core functionality of the Platform.</li>
<li>Technical data that the Participant’s computer transmits as part of its interactions with the Platform, depending on the Participant’s device setup. These technical data may include things like IP-address, browser information and device settings.</li>
<li> Authentication data entered by the Participant during the authentication process or the Organizer in advance, typically email address, phone number, zip code and/or name </li>
<li> Login data entered by the Organizer; </li>
</ul>
<p> Stanford and SCDT will not share any personally identifiable information of Participants collected by the Platform without your explicit consent. By accessing and using the Platform, each User explicitly consents and agrees to participating in the applicable Process as described below and the collection and use of the Platform’s data streams and transcripts as described in these TOS and that the such data and the transcripts may be collected, used and shared by Stanford and SCDT (or by the Platform directly):
</p>
<ul>
<li>to provide, operate and support the Platform and associated services; to improve and modify the Platform and do Platform-related performance analysis and improvement; </li>
<li> to conduct and publish the results of the Research, and any other research or teaching purposes within Stanford’s purview, provided that any included Participant data will be in aggregated, de-identified or anonymized form so that it does not include personally identifiable information; </li>
<li> as required to comply with any legal or regulatory process or requirement (e.g. a subpoena), to enforce these TOS, or to pursue available legal remedies or defend against legal claims; and </li>
<li> with the Organizer during the Process (and thereafter as described below) for its use for authentication and as a record of the Process and its proceedings. </li>
</ul>

<p> The Organizer bears sole responsibility for seeking consent from the Participant for any further sharing of personally identifiable information that the Organizer receives from Stanford, SDCT the Platform or otherwise collects, observes, or requests, including that observed, collected, or requested by any of Organizer’s administrators, employees, vendors, agents or observers that have been provided access to the Platform by Organizer or at its request. SCDT will provide any Organizer or Participant with a more detailed list of the types of data the Platform collects for any use of the Platform that pertains to the applicable Process, upon request.
</p>
<p> SCDT will not directly contact the Participants for any purpose unless approved by the Organizer, except in the following two cases:</p>
<ul>
<li> Providing technical support to the Participants in case of technical difficulties </li>
<li> Follow-up survey with explicit consent of the Participants</li>
</ul>

<p> By making the Platform available to Participants, Organizer represents and warrants that it shall use all User data it receives via the Platform and/or from Stanford or SCDT in accordance with all applicable laws and in accordance with Organizer’s privacy policy for its website.
